    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-08-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="494"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d494">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Scruggs</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-08-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 30, 1892</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 278.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Upon the receipt of your telegram of the 22d
                    instant, asking that a vessel of the U. S. Navy be dispatched forthwith to La
                    Guayra, I communicated copy thereof to the Secretary of the Navy.</p>
                <p>Pending arrangments to dispatch a vessel, the arrival of the mail steamer <hi
                        rend="italic">Caracas</hi> on the 26th brought dispatches from your legation
                    and our consuls throwing light upon the urgency of your request.</p>
                <p>In regard to the reported taking of six passengers from the steamer <hi
                        rend="italic">Caracas</hi>, at Puerto Cabello, by order of Gen. Urdaneta,
                    the Department awaits full particulars of the occurrence before giving you
                    positive instructions.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
